main.formObjects

Class FMS

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.formObjects.FMS

  • public class FMS
extends java.lang.Object
    FMS Score Sheet Model Object.

    It represents the form used to score each athlete.

    It contains a total of 10 tests and uses their final score to generate a final report or score.

        Constructor for the class.

        Sets all variables under the "Raw Score" and "Final Score" sections. Additionally, sets the comments to be cleared out

        Parameters:
        deepSquatRaw - Raw score for the deep squat test
        hurdleStepRawL - Raw score for the left for the hurdle step test
        hurdleStepRawR - Raw score for the right for the hurdle step test
        inlineLoungeRawL - Raw score for the left for the inline lounge test
        inlineLoungeRawR - Raw score for the right for the inline lounge test
        shoulderMobilityRawL - Raw score for the left for the shoulder mobility test
        shoulderMobilityRawR - Raw score for the right for the shoulder mobility test
        shoulderClearingL - Raw score for the left for the shoulder clearing test
        shoulderClearingR - Raw score for the right for the shoulder clearing test
        legRaiseRawL - Raw score for the left for the active straight-leg raise test
        legRaiseRawR - Raw score for the right for the active straight-leg raise test
        trunkStabilityRaw - Raw score for the Trunk Stability Push-Up test
        extensionClearing - Boolean raw score for the extension clearing test
        rotaryRawL - Raw score for the left for the rotary stability test
        rotaryRawR - Raw score for the right for the rotary stability test
        flexionClearing - Boolean raw score for the flexion clearing test
        total - Total final score for the FMS Score Sheet

      • addRow

        public void addRow(boolean viewInfo,
                   java.lang.String DBindex)
        Adds a row to the database class. It is used in conjunction with the other forms, since the value for each table is autoincremented.
        Parameters:
        viewInfo - Boolean value for if you should insert the data into the database (false), or if you should update the athlete in the database (true)
        DBindex - Index of the athlete in the database. The Athlete's ID. Used when updating the athlete in teh database (when the viewInfo param holds value of true)
